Sentence: The doctor who treated me was very kind.
The : definite article, specifies "doctor"
doctor : common noun, singular, antecedent of the relative clause
who : relative pronoun, refers to "doctor", introduces a restrictive clause
treated : verb, past tense, action performed by "who"
me : personal pronoun, object of "treated"
was : linking verb, past tense
very : adverb, modifies "kind"
kind : adjective, subject complement describing "doctor"

Sentence: My car, which is ten years old, still runs perfectly.
My : possessive determiner, modifies "car"
